Alembic schema migrations for AlphaLens.

There are no SQLAlchemy ORM models in this codebase (the app uses raw SQL via
sqlite3/psycopg, see services/api/app/core/database.py), so revisions are
hand-written raw SQL rather than autogenerated.

env.py resolves the target database the same way the API process does:
DATABASE_URL (Postgres/Neon) when set, otherwise the local SQLite file at
ALPHALENS_DATABASE_PATH (default data/alphalens.db).

Common commands (run from the repository root):

    # apply all pending migrations to whichever DB is currently configured
    alembic upgrade head

    # apply migrations to Neon specifically
    DATABASE_URL=postgresql://... alembic upgrade head

    # create a new revision after changing the schema
    alembic revision -m "add some_column to strategy_drafts"

The app's own startup bootstrap (services/api/app/core/database.py::
initialize_schema) still runs CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS on every process
start for backward compatibility, so `alembic upgrade head` is always a safe
no-op against an already-bootstrapped database. New schema changes should be
added as Alembic revisions instead of growing that bootstrap function.
